<script data-webtasks-id="23a29be4-80ac-40a7" style="">
  function prepareUrl(params) {
    const url = new URL(location.href)
    const queryParams = new URLSearchParams(location.search)
    let customUrl = url.protocol + "//" + url.hostname + url.pathname
    for (const paramName of params) {
      const paramValue = queryParams.get(paramName)
      if (paramValue) customUrl = customUrl + '/' + paramValue
    }
    return customUrl + location.search
  }
  plausible('pageview', { u: prepareUrl(["id"]) })
</script>

    <h2 class="title" data-webtasks-id="e054c364-3506-4c42"><a alt="Laughter as medicine: a systematic review and meta-analysis of interventional studies evaluating the impact of spontaneous laughter on cortisol levels" href="/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0286260" data-webtasks-id="2c7a58e3-8189-4291">Laughter as medicine: a systematic review and meta-analysis of interventional studies evaluating the impact of spontaneous laughter on cortisol levels</a></h2>

     <p data-webtasks-id="6c5d273d-fab7-4e96">Kramer and Leitao explore the healing power of laughter. Their findings reveal that spontaneous laughter induces a significant reduction in cortisol levels, offering potential benefits for enhancing overall well-being.</p>
